        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 1:29PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 128 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
southeast of Westville, moving northeast at 40 mph. Another strong
thunderstorm was located near Walnut Hill, moving northeast at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Northwest Arkansas Regional Air...Beaver Lake...
Cincinnati...                     Savoy...
Tontitown...                      Larue...
Pea Ridge...                      Cave Springs...
Wedington...                      Pleasant Ridge...
Hobbs State Park...               Best...
Lincoln...                        Clifty...
Busch...                          War Eagle...
Highfill...                       Monte Ne...
Healing Springs...                Farmington...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 58 and 90.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
